qas.question: Why were the prince electors able to proclaim themselves King of Prussia?

answers.text: Because the duchy was outside of the core Holy Roman Empire

qas.question: In what year were the prince electors elect them selves as King?
What time period did East Prussia and West Prussia join to become Prussia?
In what year was the Holy Roman Empire founded?
What type of government entity was Prussia prior to 1773?
How could those in eastern Prussia get to the rest of the Prussian State prior to 1772?
How was the Holy Roman Empire connected to Brandenburg?

context: <a0_0>Because the duchy was outside of the core Holy Roman Empire<a0_0/>, the prince-electors of Brandenburg were able to proclaim themselves King of Prussia beginning in <a1_0><b3_0>1701<b3_0/><a1_0/>. After the annexation of most of western Royal Prussia in the First Partition of the Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth in 1772, eastern (ducal) Prussia was connected <b5_0><b6_0>by land<b6_0/><b5_0/> with the rest of the Prussian state and was reorganized as a <b4_0>province<b4_0/> the following year (1773). Between 1829 and 1878, the Province of East Prussia was joined with West Prussia to form the Province of <a2_0>Prussia<a2_0/>.
